6 years ago today.. it was just me and Nashy. I always brought him to work with me. Just about 2 weeks before meeting @dobrojosh and he understood we were a package deal. 😆

Now, Nashys about to have his third baby brother..🤍
All cozy and ready for Christmas! I love them so much!🎄🤍

Here we are at #38 weeks 🤰🏽.. wobbling to the finish line and feeling. So. ready. 👏🏼

We have a name! Any guesses? Hint: keeping the Bible theme going.

Merry Christmas from our family to yours! May we never get distracted and always keep our savior Jesus at the center of this day.. and every day. 🤍🎄 

“For to us a child is born, to us a son is given, and the government will be on his shoulders. And he will be called Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace” -Isaiah 9:6
My Jonah.. soaking in the last few days as the baby of our family. I love you more than life. 🤍, momma

Just like that, we are changed forever again. 

Our Elijah Rain 💙
11:26 am January 13th, 2023
8 lbs, 7oz
21.5”

It was a beautiful home water birth right as the snow came falling down outside our window.. a moment I longed and prayed for. Birth is a surrender and better left alone when all is healthy.. even if you wait a couple of weeks passed your due date. 😅

Trust your body, baby and Gods timing. We are soaking in these precious moments with our family and just so grateful to have Elijah in our arms. Thank you Jesus for this beautiful gift. 😭🤍🙏🏼
I love you.

Happy 5th Birthday to my sweet Noah! I’m so proud of the little boy you are and becoming. Your smile lights up the room and your soccer rocker skills blow us away. 😁I pray you always keep the Lord and His truth front and center in your life. Dad and I will always be your biggest cheerleaders and support you along the journey of life. I love you so much! ♥️
My forever valentine.. I love you. 🤍
First Valentine’s with you.. my Elijah Rain. 😘
My whole 🌎🤍

Happy 3rd Birthday to the LIGHT of my life. My sweet Jonah, you and your dimples light up my world. ☺️I pray you always hold the Lord close and stand firm in His truth. I love you with my whole heart and there’s nothing you can ever do to change that. ♥️, mommy

5 weeks of holding our sweet Elijah! I love your double chin, little whimpers when you’re dreaming….. oh and the chunky rolls ☺️

From time to time I share products that bring our family value. Going from 2 to 3 has been a major adjustment. We’re officially OUTNUMBERED 😂.. I take it one moment at a time and need a minimum 10 clones at any given moment.. plus 10 extra shots of expresso 😜.. Can’t make the clone thing happen BUT some things have been particularly helpful with keeping an eye on everyone. We were generously gifted this @lollipopbabycamera and it’s been so helpful in the transition.. not only for baby but to keep an eye on the boys playing upstairs when I’m feeding and full hands with Elijah downstairs. Here’s what I love: 

🍭 The full view of the room with very clear picture and sound quality.. even at night in the dark (night vision turned on) 

🍭Super easy setup and clips anywhere

🍭Links to my phone so I don’t need to lug around an extra device around the house 

🍭Special alerts with certain sounds (can distinguish between a normal sound and a cry) 

🍭soothing sounds and music to soothe everyone to sleep 

Use code ‘Daphnedeloren’ at checkout for a handy dandy discount 😊
Tired momma, happy heart.. anything for these newborn snuggles. ♥️
The Original - The REmix - MicDrop! 😍
I love you.

A very special (and rare😁) night out cheering on daddy @dobrojosh play with our talented sister @maeestes while she made her @opry debut.. she’s worked SO hard for this moment and shined brighter than the stars! Elijah and I had the best seat in the house watching from a bench at the back of the stage (last pic 👉🏼) ⭐️
First time eating out as a family of 5 ✋🏼.. started with an order of a large coffee.. sweet little man passed out in my arms and everything went just fine. 😌♥️ (swipe 👉🏼for chunky cheeks)

Jonah mommy date! We started with a fresh haircut then hit the mall.. I love my boy so much! To all my mommas out there with a new baby in the house, these one on one dates with the older ones are everything! ♥️

He is RISEN! The greatest gift, hope and peace for the believer.. He paid it all and now we get to spend eternity with our savior. I can’t wait for that day.. truly unimaginable. 

Happy Resurrection Day from our family to yours! Also.. no one said this life was easy.. let our family snapshot be LIVING PROOF. 😂.. going in the memoirs.
My Elijah 🤍.. first time celebrating Resurrection Day. I love this boy!
Our sweet Elijah.. 3 months old. We love you so much! 🤍
My sweet Jonah, I love watching your little personality blossom. ☺️
“I go super fast mom” #wakeupchatswithJonah

Motherhood. 

The greatest gift. 

The greatest, hardest, most fulfilling, most exhausting, most rewarding gift of my life. Before I had children, I thought a stay at home mom had to be the easiest job there is.. wrong is an understatement. Oh Daph. 😂🙏🏼it’s harder work then anything out there for a lot less pay but the reward is greater than any dollar bill sign. 

Motherhood changed my goals and priorities overnight. It’s my greatest work and responsibility.. raising these boys to know His truth and become men of God. That is my deepest hope and prayer. That they see through the darkness and deception of a very real enemy on this earth.. that they focus on the unseen real important things. Until I go to the grave, that is my greatest mission. I pray for grace along the way.. because I fall short.. plenty. 

Happy Mother’s Day to all the incredible mommas out there! 🤍
My sweet Noah, how I love you. Thanks for making me a momma. 🤍
Story time before bedtime.. always a special time. I love my little honeys! ♥️
Every day (really every moment 😂) is an adventure with them. 🤍🍃
I love you. 🤍
We made a boy band! 🤍 #3muskateers
Reunited and it feels so good. 🤍
Hey mom! I caught my first fish! 🎣 (Well.. my first one without @dobrojosh help 😂)

A lady I didn’t know was passing by our dinner table at a pizza restaurant tonight. She looked at me and asked me where my phone was. I pointed to the table, she grabbed it and said you’ll want this capture one day then started to snap away. It was a sweet moment. Normally people are in their own world so it meant a lot. 

You, my sweet boy, will never be too old to fall asleep in mommy’s arms. 🤍

It was a beautiful day celebrating LOVE! Congrats to our cuzzys Connor and Elise to tying the knot! Love that you keep the Lord front most and center in your relationship and lives. You found the KEY. 🤍🔑

You may have a few more gray hairs but you will ALWAYS be our baby! Happy 7th Birthday to our Nashy pie! You bring our family so much JOY and unconditional LOVE. It used to be just you and me.. now you have a dad and 3 brothers who absolutely adore you. I love you so much! 🤍🥳
One day we’ll say.. those were the good ‘ol summer days. ☀️💦
My little country boy.. 🍃😍

Happy Fathers Day to the best daddy in the world! It’s been so beautiful watching you go from becoming a dad to leading our three little honeys. There’s been A LOT of spit up showers, sleepless nights and navigating obstacles over the last 5 years but you’ve worn it proudly, sacrificed greatly and handled each day with grace. These boys and I are truly blessed to have you lead us. I love the life and family we’ve created.. and I’m in love with you. ♥️

Soaking up every moment with you.. by baby #3 there’s a realization of how fleeting time is and how precious it truly is. No matter what you do, you can’t get it back. This round has no doubt been the most challenging but through the tough moments or sleepless nights, I’ve found my approach different this time.. filled with more patience because I know I’ll blink and he’ll be 5 just like my Noah. I love you so much, my little E. 🤍
So in love with you.. and your eyebrow raises.. and your cheeks.. and your smile.. and your blueberry face. 🫐
6 years married to my honey today. You are the sweetest soul I’ve ever known. So honored to be your wife. I love you with all of my heart. 🤍
Proud to be an AMERICAN 🇺🇸
Happy 4th from our little crew to yours!! 🇺🇸♥️🤍💙

My honey turns 41 today! The day I met him, I thought he was the sweetest guy I had ever met... but then I thought time would truly tell because people can fool you.. and he sure passed the time test. He is still the sweetest guy, best dad, hardest worker, the most talented dobro player and truly the most humble guy. There’s not a person who knows him that doesn’t love him. Please help me wish @dobrojosh a Happy Birthday! I love you so much, honey! ♥️🥳

Watching you discover the world (and almond butter/banana treats) is a beautiful thing. 🤍

My babies first day of Kindergarten.. thought I had it all together but sure enough lost it just as we were dropping him off. 😭♥️I feel like we just brought our baby home from the hospital. He did so great! 

Homeschooling with a couple of days a week at a hybrid school is the route our family has chosen for schooling.. we are so excited to see how it all plays out!

My grandma is 93 and the sweetest woman in the world. As a little girl, I used to hear her night time prayers because she’d say them out loud (in Turkish). She prayed the Lord would let her see my children before she passed. We surprised her this weekend and she got to meet the ones she hasn’t yet.. our Jonah and Elijah. It was so special and I’ll treasure it forever. She said now she can rest easy going home. I love her so much. 😭♥️

He told Dolly “Dolly, you send me books every month” and she said “I sure do darling. I hope you’re enjoying them.” One for the books! 😊

What a time to be alive. My heart is so heavy. The worlds heart is heavy. 

There’s a war going on in Israel.. there’s also a war going on for every soul on earth. Let all of this chaos be a reminder, life on earth is but a mist. We don’t know when our last breath will be. It could be death from the result of war, or driving down the road and getting in an accident. Every heart beat will stop one day. Eternity is real. Heaven is real and so is hell. We’re talking about eternity in one or the other. It’s time to get real about your salvation and the salvation of others. Please don’t put it off. Jesus is the only way. 

“For all have sinned and fall short of the Glory of God” -Romans 3:23

“For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God us eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord” -Romans 6:23 

“But God shows His love for us in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us” -Romans 5:8

“For everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved” -Romans 10:18 

“Because, if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart God raised him from the dead, you will be saved. For with the heart one believes and is justified, and with the mouth one confesses and is saved” -Romans 10:9-10
Fall is our favorite! First pumpkin patch adventures for our littlest pumpkin, Elijah. Thank you Lord, for these precious gifts. I love them so much. ♥️🍂

Greatest lesson learned over 32 years: With Jesus, you have everything. Without Him, you have nothing. He is the way, the truth and the life. Life on earth is a mist. Eternity is forever.

It’s rare when I’m able to get out and watch my honey do what he does best. I’m usually holding down the fort at home. When I do get the chance, I treasure it that much more and I’m reminded how talented he is but even more, how humble he is. Such a special night watching Josh, Mae and Dustin play the Grand Ole Opry. 

It was Jonah and Elijah’s first time in the circle (swipe 👉🏼). So proud of you, honey! 🤍

One year ago today, I held you in my arms for the first time with tear filled eyes. It was a beautiful home water birth and peaceful as I watched snow hitting our window sill, holding me through one contraction at a time. Oh how the Lord knew I needed my Elijah. Your infectious giggle is unlike anything I’ve ever heard and it has been my daily medicine. When we’re out and about, that giggle turns heads and I witness instant joy with strangers. It makes me SMILE. I absolutely adore you and have the deepest gratitude that the Lord has blessed our family with you. My greatest prayer for your life is that you will find God and His truth at an early age. Jesus is the way, the truth and the life. It’s all in the Bible, our living water. It’s a dark world baby but we have eternal hope in Him. I love you more than you could ever imagine and I will always be there for my little E. 

♥️,
Mommy
